SR:
I encounter a MissingResourceException when attempting to create a FontRegistry instance for my application. The code snippet I am using is as follows: com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
	FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I have confirmed that I do have a file named fonts.properties located in com/company/product/ folder. However, if I use the ResourceBundle class instead, as shown in the following code snippet:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
	ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

No exception is thrown. Additionally, if I make a complete copy of the FontRegistry class in my com.company.product package, it works. Based on my observations, I suspect that this is a bug in the FontRegistry class.
